# Terminal Commands
1. ls --> list all files and directories in the current directory
2. pwd --> present working directory
3. cd --> change directory
4. cd .. --> move to the parent directory
5. clear --> clear the terminal
6. cd / --> move to the root directory
7. cd ~ --> move to the home directory
8. open . --> open the current directory in the finder
9. mkdir name --> make a new directory with the name 'name'
10. touch name --> create a new file with the name 'name'
11. open name --> open the file with the name 'name'
12. open -a "application name" name --> open the file with the name 'name' in the application 'application name'
13. mv name1 name2 --> rename the file with the name 'name1' to 'name2'
14. rm name --> remove the file with the name 'name'
15. rm -r name --> remove the directory with the name 'name'
16. say "text" --> speak the text